  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The clinical use case has grown since the original validation campaign to include paediatric and neonatal patient populations with flow rates of 0.3–1.2 L/min, extending well below the 2.0–6.0 L/min adult range validated in 2019. No re-calibration or supplemental validation evidence covering the expanded low-flow regime has been linked to this package.",
